The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Highlights
                                                   Highlights
                            
	Gautam Gambhirs marathon innings of 137 in 642 minutes and 436 balls was the longest innings (in terms of minutes) by an Indian against New Zealand (previous best: 222 in 578 minutes by Rahul Dravid in Ahmedabad, October 2003).         
	Gambhir was the first Indian to bat over 500 minutes and 400 balls in New Zealand.         
	Gambhirs innings was the second longest (in terms of minutes) by an Indian outside the sub-continent (best: 201 in 673 minutes by Navjot Singh Sidhu at Port of Spain, March 1997).         
	It was the fifth longest (in terms of minutes) by a visiting batsman on New Zealand soil.         
	V.V.S. Laxmans century was his 14th in Tests. It was his second against New Zealand and first in New Zealand.         
	It was his second century while following on and eighth away from home.         
	Yuvraj Singhs 54 .. was his first fifty outside the sub-continent in 16 innings.         
	Indias 476 for four is now the highest score made by a team following on in New Zealand.         
	Indias total is now their third highest while following on after 657/7 decl. (against Aus in Calcutta, 2001) and 510 (against Eng in Leeds, 1967). Incidentally, India won at Calcutta but lost in Leeds.         
	This is the eighth occasion on which India have drawn a Test match after being made to follow-on.         
	India became the first visiting team in NZ to draw a Test match after being forced to follow-on. Before this match, NZ had won all seven Tests at home after enforcing the follow-on.           COMPILED BY MOHANDAS MENON                                                                                                                   
